  { question: "How does IDR forgiveness work?", answer: "Income-Driven Repayment plans cap your monthly payment at a percentage of your discretionary income. After 20 years (for undergraduate loans) or 25 years (for graduate loans) of qualifying payments, any remaining balance is forgiven. Unlike PSLF, the forgiven amount under IDR may be subject to federal income tax." },
