  { question: "Will I owe taxes on forgiven student loan amounts?", answer: "Under PSLF, forgiven amounts are tax-free. Under IDR forgiveness after 20 or 25 years, the forgiven balance may be treated as taxable income by the IRS. However, the American Rescue Plan Act temporarily exempts student loan forgiveness from federal tax through 2025." },
